ove the observability stack. First, ensure critical node-level metrics, especially for disk space and inodes, are being collected for all nodes. Second, review and tune the anomaly detection thresholds for these fundamental metrics to ensure they trigger alerts before resource exhaustion leads to failure. Finally, investigate methods to correlate widespread secondary alerts to a single root cause to reduce noise during future incidents.\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
