reGc_used.C metric (2) and container memory failures from 09:28 to 09:29 CST.",\n    "Related Entities": ["adservice2.ts:8088", "node-5.shippingservice-1"],\n    "Features": ["garbage collection issues", "container memory failures"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\nRelevant Historical Incidents (if any):\n[Past Incident 1] (Score: 0.501)\nComponent: recommendationservice | Metrics: CPU, gRPC, load, memory, rt, trace, utilization\nSummary: Component: recommendationservice\nEvent: recommendationservice failure at 2022-03-20 12:10:57\nSystem Type: Banking Microservice (service)\nSymptoms: container CPU load; The Trace Anomaly Report shows a \'frequency\' anomaly for calls from \'recommendationservice-1\' to \'productcatalogservice-1\' for the method \'hipstershop.ProductCatalogService/ListProducts\', starting at ; The Metric Mesh Anomaly Report indicates an anomaly in \'istio_agent_go_memstats_mspan_inuse_bytes\' for \'recommendationservice-0\' at 12:11:00 CST. This reflects increased memory activity within the ser\nAffected Metrics: CPU, gRPC, load, memory, rt, trace, utilization\nRoot Cause Category: The \'container CPU load\' failure in \'recommendationservice\' was caused by an anomalous increase in the frequency of outbound gRPC calls to \'productcat\nFailure Pattern: The \'container CPU load\' failure in \'recommendationservice\' was caused by an anomalous increase in the frequency of outbound gRPC calls to \'productcatalogservice\'. This surge in requests to list products significantly increased the processing workload and consequently the CPU utilization of the \'recommendationservice\' container, leading to resource exhaustion.\nMitigation Principles: 1. Investigate the application logic within \'recommendationservice\' to identify the trigger for the sudden increase in calls to \'productcatalogservice\'. 2. Implement rate limiting or circuit breaking for this specific call path to prevent cascading failures. 3. Enhance monitoring by adding specific alerts on the call frequency between \'recommendationservice\' and \'productcatalogservice\'. 4. Review and adjust the sensitivity of the container-level CPU metric anomaly detection to ensure direct symptoms of CPU load are captured in future incidents.\n\nBackgroud:\n"\n\n\nBased on this information, identify the MOST LIKELY root cause component and reason from the candidate list.\nFollow these rules:\n- The root cause must be a single component from the candidate list.\n- The reason must be directly supported by the anomaly description.\n- Assign a suspicious score between 0.0 and 1.0 (higher = more confident).\n\nRespond ONLY with a JSON object in this exact format:\n{\n    "component": "service-name",\n    "reason": "brief reason",\n    "score": 0.92\n}'}]
