ement exponential backoff with jitter, preventing CPU-exhausting retry storms during dependency outages. 3. Enhance monitoring to include alerts for high rates of DNS errors or latency as observed from application pods, allowing for faster detection of this failure mode. 4. Consider configuring a local DNS cache on the nodes (e.g., using NodeLocal DNSCache) to improve DNS performance and reliability.", 'metadata': {'source_file': 'market_root_cause_reports_en_6mtd.jsonl', 'original_source': 'shippingservice2-0 failure at 2022-03-20 20:23:02', 'system_type': 'Banking Microservice (pod)', 'component': 'shippingservice2-0', 'metrics': ['CPU', 'GC', 'connection', 'gRPC', 'load', 'memory', 'network', 'rr', 'rt', 'socket'], 'root_cause_category': "A temporary DNS name resolution failure occurred within the cluster, as evidenced by 'UnknownHostException' logs. This infrastructure issue prevented "}, 'score': 0.5401087999343872}]
